Other features and advantages of the invention will be more readily understood upon reading the following detailed description, in conjunction with the drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 is a diagram of an imaging apparatus according to an exemplary embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 2a illustrates focusing using a conventional physical transducer;


FIG. 2b illustrates the synthetic aperture focusing technique (SAFT);


FIGS. 3a-3c illustrate synthetic aperture focusing of an extended area from a single line of scan points;


FIGS. 4a-4c graphically illustrate compensation of scan data with a matched filter;


FIG. 5a represents an ideal reconstructed image using SAFT;


FIG. 5b illustrates a SAFT reconstructed image without a matched filter;


FIG. 5c illustrates a SAFT reconstructed image using a matched filter; and


FIG. 6 illustrates the improved resolution which may be obtained with a matched filter and SAFT.
